Peru Stocks: Candente Copper Falls; La Cima, Panoro Increase

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-02-23T22:44:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/peru-stocks-candente-falls-panoro-and-pomalca-increase.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index fell 0.4 percent to 22,616.51. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.6 percent to 3,059.66.    Candente Copper Corp . (DNT PE), a Canadian copper
exploration company, fell 0.5 percent to $1.98. Base metal
prices declined today, with copper reaching a four week low, on
speculation that unrest in North Africa and the Middle East will
derail recovering economies as oil prices jump.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML PE), which owns a gold project in
northern Peru, gained 1.7 percent to 61 cents, the highest price
since June 2008. The price of gold rose today, heading for its
longest rally in six months, as turmoil in Libya boosted demand
for an investment haven.    Gold Fields La Cima SAA  (LACIMAI1 PE), another gold miner,
rose 1.5 percent to 3.35 soles, ending a four day losing streak.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
